# TextEditor Coding Standards

## Language & Compiler
- C17 standard (`/std:c17` on MSVC, `-std=c17` on GCC/Clang)
- Zero third-party dependencies; only C standard library and platform-native APIs
- All source files are UTF-8 encoded; MSVC must compile with `/utf-8`

## File Organization
- Max ~300 lines per `.c` file; split when exceeding this
- One logical responsibility per file (single-responsibility principle)
- Header files use `#pragma once` (not `#ifndef` guards)
- Include order: system headers → project headers
- All UI strings must be ASCII-only (no multi-byte characters in display output)

## Naming
- Functions and variables: `snake_case`
- Macros and constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Global module-level state: `g_` prefix (e.g., `g_editor`, `g_sb`)
- Internal (file-scope) functions: `static` keyword required
- Type names (struct/enum): `PascalCase` via `typedef`

## Comments
- Only explain **why**, not **what** — never narrate what the code obviously does
- Bad: `/* increment counter */  i++;`
- Good: `/* wrap around to stay within DOS 80-col limit */`
- Public API functions: one-line comment above declaration in the header
- No block comments inside function bodies unless explaining a non-obvious algorithm

## Error Handling
- Functions that can fail return `int`: `0` = success, `-1` = failure
- Boolean queries return `bool`
- Never silently ignore a return value from `malloc`; use `safe_malloc()` from `util.h`
- NULL pointer parameters must be documented in the header

## Memory
- Every `malloc`/`safe_malloc` must have a matching `free` path
- Document ownership in the header: who allocates, who frees
- Prefer stack allocation for buffers < 4 KB

## Constants
- Use `MAKE_ATTR(fg, bg)` from `types.h` instead of raw hex for color attributes
- Named constants over magic numbers; define in `types.h` or the relevant header

## Build
- CMake is the sole build system (`CMakeLists.txt` in project root)
- Quick build: `cmake_build.bat` (Windows) or `cmake --build cmake-build`
- Tests: `cmake_build.bat test` — must pass 0 failures before any commit
- Build artifacts go in `cmake-build/`; never commit this directory

## Testing
- Every new public function in `src/` needs at least one test case in `tests/`
- Tests use the self-implemented framework in `tests/test_runner.h` (no third-party)
- Mock display via `tests/mocks/mock_display.c`; do not link real display in tests
